        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 3:11PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 310 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles north of Walhalla, or 5 miles southeast of Highlands, moving
southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pine Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
